 Moeti Mmusi of the Department of Community Safety, Security and Liason said that the accident occurred on Saturday 27 April when a double cab bakkie and a sedan collided head on at around 18:00. A second sedan crashed into the two vehicles thereafter.  Three women and a man were declared dead on the scene whilst five people were taken to hospital with serious injuries. The drivers of both vehicles were among those seriously injured. The man who passed away on the scene had to be cut out of the wreckage by emergency personnel. A female patient passed away due to her injuries on Monday morning, raising the death toll to five.  The names of the deceased have not been made public yet.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 